description: Made fresh to order. These organic strawberries are so healthy and delicious. They are simply strawberries. We do not add any sweeteners or preservatives. Just the natural sweet taste of fresh strawberries.   These  strawberries are better than those you might know from your morning cereal.

Organic pineapple is a delicious and healthy snack. Grown without pesticide and chemical free, all natural organic pineapple hand sliced contain no added sweeteners or preservatives. They are an excellent source of dietary fiber, enzymes, and antioxidants and provide a major health boost. It’s also a good source of antioxidants, the protective compounds that defend cells against damaging free radicals. Antioxidants may reduce the risk for age-related degeneration and disease. organic pineapple is rich in enzymes. One enzyme in particular, bromelain, is effective at reducing inflammation, relieving indigestion, and improving the immune system. That’s a whole lot of health benefits in this tasty organic pineapple.

Organic kiwi are deliciously and slightly tangy taste. These dried kiwi are hand sliced have a vibrant green color that is so much fun to look at, but even better to eat. Organic Dried kiwi are natural digestive aid packed with enzymes, fiber, and potassium, to keep electrolytes in check. They are also a good source of protective antioxidants and immunity-boosting vitamins. Enjoy them as a healthy snack or dip them in chocolate for a real treat!

Fresh dried! Organic Barhi dates are small and somewhat chewy texture. This gorgeous dates are grown in Florida without chemical. Dates are  known for having a sinfully sweet, but not this one. Raw dried dates are like caramel candy not sugary at all. Our superb Barhis are preserved without sulphur dioxide for a natural delight you’ll celebrate.

MORINGA SEEDS ARE OBTAINED FROM THE PODS OF THE MORINGA PLANT (MORINGA OLEIFERA) OR THE DRUMSTICK TREE, NATIVE TO NORTHERN INDIA. FRESH AND RAW MORINGA SEEDS ARE QUITE TENDER, BUT AS SOON AS THEY GET DRIED, THEY BECOME HARD AND START TO RESEMBLE SMALL BEANS. THEY ARE GREYISH-WHITE IN COLOR WITH UNIQUE WING-LIKE STRUCTURES. THEY CAN BE STEAMED, BOILED OR ROASTED FOR VARIOUS PURPOSES.
